@victory_1872
title: Republicans win the 1872 election!
subtitle: Republicans: [+ repEVTotal +] electoral votes
view-if: potus_winner = "rep"
on-arrival: {!
    Q.president = Q.Candidate;
    Q.president_party = "rep";
    Q.liberal_split = 0; // Liberal Republicans largely return to fold after defeat
    Q.liberal_reunion_triggered = 1;
!}

The Republicans have won the election. 

[? if Candidate = "Grant" : Grant's victory is a resounding endorsement of his first term. The Liberal Republican revolt has been crushed at the polls. Greeley, humiliated by his catastrophic defeat, will not long survive it — he dies within weeks of the election, a broken man. ?]

[? if Candidate = "Wade" : Wade's Radical coalition has held together long enough to win. The Liberal Republicans are routed. Reconstruction enters a new, more forceful phase. ?]

[? if Candidate = "Chase" : Chase wins a second term, vindicating his moderate course. The Radicals are displeased but powerless. The Liberal Republican challenge has collapsed. ?]

[? if Candidate = "Blaine" : James Blaine carries the Republican banner to victory. The new president will chart his own course, distinct from the Radical era. ?]

[? if Candidate = "Conkling" : Roscoe Conkling, the New York machine boss, has won the presidency. The spoils system is safe for another four years. ?]

[? if greeley_fusion = 1 : Despite the unified opposition of Democrats and Liberal Republicans, the Republican machine proved too strong. The fusion experiment has failed. ?]

@defeat_dem_1872
title: The Democrats have won the presidency.
subtitle: Democrats: [+ demEVTotal +] electoral votes
view-if: potus_winner = "dem" and greeley_fusion = 0
on-arrival: president = dem_candidate_1872; president_party = "dem";

[? if dem_candidate_1872 = "Hancock" : General Hancock's formidable coalition of Democrats and disaffected Republicans has carried enough states to deny the Republicans an electoral majority. The soldier who held the line at Gettysburg now takes the White House. Reconstruction faces an uncertain future under a Democratic president. ?]

[? if dem_candidate_1872 = "Thurman" : The "Old Roman" has pulled off a stunning upset. Thurman's Ohio base proved decisive, and the Democrats have reclaimed the White House for the first time since Buchanan. ?]

[? if dem_candidate_1872 = "Bayard" : Bayard's conservative coalition has won enough Southern and border states to reach the presidency. It is the end of the Radical Reconstruction era. ?]

[? if dem_candidate_1872 = "Pendleton" : Pendleton's Greenback platform has mobilized an unlikely coalition of debtors, farmers, and workers sufficient to reach the White House. The financial establishment is in a panic. ?]

@defeat_greeley_fusion
title: The Greeley fusion ticket has won!
subtitle: Liberal Republicans/Democrats: [+ libEVTotal +] electoral votes
view-if: potus_winner = "lib" and greeley_fusion = 1
on-arrival: president = "Greeley"; president_party = "lib"; liberal_split = 0;

The impossible has happened. The combined Democratic and Liberal Republican coalition has carried enough states to deny the Republicans an electoral majority. Horace Greeley — the eccentric editor who spent decades denouncing the Democratic Party — will be the next President of the United States, carried there on Democratic votes.

The victory is bittersweet for everyone. Democrats feel they have swallowed a bitter pill. Liberal Republicans are triumphant but uncertain whether Greeley can govern. The Republican Party, for the first time since the war, finds itself locked out of the White House. Reconstruction's future hangs in the balance.

@defeat_greeley_independent
title: The Liberal Republicans have won!
subtitle: Liberal Republicans: [+ libEVTotal +] electoral votes
view-if: potus_winner = "lib" and greeley_fusion = 0
on-arrival: president = "Greeley"; president_party = "lib"; liberal_split = 0;

In a stunning three-way upset, Horace Greeley and the Liberal Republicans have won an electoral majority without Democratic fusion. The split opposition vote has somehow broken in Greeley's favor. The Republican Party is shattered, and Reconstruction faces an uncertain future under a president who campaigned on ending military occupation of the South.

@house_decides_1872
title: No majority — the election goes to the House!
subtitle: Rep: [+ repEVTotal +] | Dem: [+ demEVTotal +] | Lib: [+ libEVTotal +]
view-if: potus_winner = "house"
on-arrival: {!
  if (Q.house_majority >= 2) {
    Q.potus_winner = "rep";
    Q.president = Q.Candidate;
    Q.president_party = "rep";
  } else if (Q.dem_r > Q.rep_r) {
    Q.potus_winner = "dem";
    Q.president = Q.dem_candidate_1872;
    Q.president_party = "dem";
  } else {
    Q.potus_winner = "rep";
    Q.president = Q.Candidate;
    Q.president_party = "rep";
  }
!}

No candidate has secured a majority of electoral votes. Under the Constitution, the election is thrown to the House of Representatives, where each state delegation casts a single vote.

[? if house_majority >= 2 : With Republicans controlling a majority of state delegations, the House elects [+ Candidate +] as President. ?]
[? if house_majority < 2 : The Democratic-leaning delegations carry the day. [+ dem_candidate_1872 +] is elected President by the House. ?]

@defeat_O_1872
title: Something has gone very wrong.
view-if: potus_winner = "other"
on-arrival: president = "???"; president_party = "???";

This outcome was not supposed to be possible. Someone has been tampering with the console.

